column3: This charming man is quite panicked.
Slay the bear attacking the foolhardy man.
You there! Please, help my friend. He's been set upon by a bear!
You'll find him to the west of here.
You'll find my friend to the west of here.
That was a little too close for my liking. Thanks for saving me.
You were asked to help by my friend? Would you head back and tell him I'm safe? I need to catch my breath first before I try to go anywhere.
Please head back and tell my friend I am safe.
He is safe? Phew, I could not be more relieved. We often have no choice but to venture outside the village in search of wild plants.
If only the bleeding earth we stand upon was more hospitable. We'd never have to put ourselves in such danger.
Regardless, all that matters is that my friend is safe. Thank you.
